{"title":"Google signs contract for small modular nuclear reactors","link":"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/906229382/0/marginalrevolution~Google-signs-contract-for-small-modular-nuclear-reactors.html","date":1728992033000,"content":"<blockquote><p>Since pioneering the first corporate purchase agreements for renewable electricity over a decade ago, Google has played a pivotal role in accelerating clean energy solutions, including the next generation of <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://sustainability.google/reports/accelerating-advanced-clean-electricity-technologies/\" target=\"_blank\">advanced clean technologies</a>. Today, we’re building on these efforts by signing the world’s first corporate agreement to purchase nuclear energy from multiple small modular reactors (SMRs) to be developed by <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://kairospower.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Kairos Power</a>. The initial phase of work is intended to bring Kairos Power’s first SMR online quickly and safely by 2030, followed by additional reactor deployments through 2035. Overall, this deal will enable up to 500 MW of new 24/7 carbon-free power to U.S. electricity grids and help more communities benefit from clean and affordable nuclear power.</p></blockquote>\r\n<p>Here is <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://blog.google/outreach-initiatives/sustainability/google-kairos-power-nuclear-energy-agreement/\" target=\"_blank\">more from Google</a>.</p>\r\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://marginalrevolution.com/marginalrevolution/2024/10/google-signs-contract-for-small-modular-nuclear-reactors.html\">Google signs contract for small modular nuclear reactors</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://marginalrevolution.com\">Marginal REVOLUTION</a>.</p>\r\n<img height=\"1\" width=\"1\" 